Reasoning: The paper discusses compressive sensing (CS) and its application to sparse signal recovery with redundant dictionaries. The paper focuses on a variant of the CoSaMP algorithm and utilizes the D-RIP condition on the sensing matrix. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of CS. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in simulations, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of heuristics, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
